1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,186
Previously on Veronica Mars...

2
00:00:02,187 --> 00:00:05,512
Man had good taste. Let's honour him
by putting his killer behind bars.

3
00:00:05,513 --> 00:00:06,749
You're off the case, Mr. Mars.

4
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:10,344
You can fire me, Mrs. O'Dell, but I'm
afraid you can't take me off the case.

5
00:00:10,345 --> 00:00:13,141
Coach Barry was found murdered
last night beside the PCH.

6
00:00:13,142 --> 00:00:14,274
Sheriff suspects Josh...

7
00:00:14,275 --> 00:00:16,630
It's Mason. Why else
would he lie? It makes sense.

8
00:00:16,631 --> 00:00:19,853
You really think that I would kill my
coach because he wasn't starting me?

9
00:00:19,854 --> 00:00:23,036
Here you go, sheriff-approved
reading material.

10
00:00:23,037 --> 00:00:26,541
Miss Mars. You are under arrest

11
00:00:26,542 --> 00:00:30,184
for the aiding and abetting
of the escape of Josh Barry.

12
00:00:31,858 --> 00:00:33,089
Where is he, Veronica?

13
00:00:33,090 --> 00:00:34,013
Where's Josh?

14
00:00:34,014 --> 00:00:36,751
Think back, Sheriff.
Where did you have him last?

15
00:00:36,752 --> 00:00:39,107
Josh's cellmate says you snuck
him a peanut-butter cookie.

16
00:00:39,108 --> 00:00:42,599
And he bribed one of your
deputies with said cookie?

17
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,771
He was allergic, but you know that.

18
00:00:44,772 --> 00:00:47,746
After the paramedic revived him
with an epinephrine shot,

19
00:00:47,781 --> 00:00:50,509
Josh overpowered him and escaped
out of the back of the ambulance.

20
00:00:50,510 --> 00:00:52,193
You didn't have a deputy with him?

21
00:00:53,216 --> 00:00:54,966
He was riding up front.

22
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:58,106
As his accomplice, I would think you would
want to get yourself out of hot water

23
00:00:58,107 --> 00:00:59,507
and tell us where he is.

24
00:01:02,421 --> 00:01:04,062
Don't I get a phone call?

25
00:01:10,562 --> 00:01:11,936
Please Keith,

26
00:01:11,937 --> 00:01:13,632
find my son.

27
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:15,743
It's likely he'll try to contact you.

28
00:01:15,744 --> 00:01:18,925
When he does, you've got to
convince him to turn himself into me.

29
00:01:18,926 --> 00:01:22,376
It will be safer than turning
himself in directly to the sheriff.

30
00:01:26,177 --> 00:01:27,974
I'll just take it in here.

31
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:33,853
Yeah?

32
00:01:33,854 --> 00:01:36,452
Keith Mars? Please hold for Veronica Mars.

33
00:01:46,458 --> 00:01:49,488
Yeah, honey, it's me.

34
00:01:51,672 --> 00:01:52,910
You're where?!

35
00:01:57,074 --> 00:02:00,374
Please, tell me you didn't help an
accused murdered to escape jail.

36
00:02:00,375 --> 00:02:02,264
Yo, pops, check it out.

37
00:02:02,265 --> 00:02:05,470
This girl ain't gonna be nobody's bitch.
You better recognise.

38
00:02:05,471 --> 00:02:06,813
What's that on your arm?

39
00:02:07,472 --> 00:02:09,235
I've had some free time.

40
00:02:09,236 --> 00:02:12,103
And, no, I didn't help Josh escape.

41
00:02:13,743 --> 00:02:15,816
Not intentionally.

42
00:02:15,817 --> 00:02:17,967
It turns out he's allergic to peanuts.

43
00:02:17,968 --> 00:02:20,942
His plan was to take
advantage of my kindness.

44
00:02:20,943 --> 00:02:23,205
That's got to be the first time
that's worked for anybody.

45
00:02:25,211 --> 00:02:26,816
Cliffod!

46
00:02:26,817 --> 00:02:28,336
Something wrong?

47
00:02:28,337 --> 00:02:31,978
I just remembered I need to return
Caged Heat to the video store.

48
00:02:31,979 --> 00:02:34,629
You folks want to hear the good
news or the bad news first?

49
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,180
I'm gonna say the good news.

50
00:02:36,181 --> 00:02:39,979
Josh's cellmate and key witness to
the cookie incident ate the evidence

51
00:02:39,980 --> 00:02:41,645
and, icing on the cake,

52
00:02:41,646 --> 00:02:44,165
blew a point two-one on the
breathalyzer when they booked him.

53
00:02:44,169 --> 00:02:46,358
No way Lamb can get a
conviction and he knows it.

54
00:02:46,359 --> 00:02:47,807
Well, that sounds like great news.

55
00:02:47,808 --> 00:02:48,872
But...

56
00:02:48,873 --> 00:02:52,274
he's gonna hold Veronica
as long as he possibly can.

57
00:02:52,818 --> 00:02:54,483
Can I get you anything, honey?

58
00:02:54,484 --> 00:02:57,514
Oh, a couple cartons of smokes.

59
00:02:58,208 --> 00:03:01,040
What, dad? It's currency on the inside.

60
00:03:02,214 --> 00:03:04,183
Any guess where I might find Josh?

61
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:05,184
Mexico?

62
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,856
So you think he did it?

63
00:03:06,857 --> 00:03:10,312
I don't know. If he didn't,
he sure panicked quickly.

64
00:03:10,313 --> 00:03:11,611
That was my thought, too.

65
00:03:11,612 --> 00:03:13,421
Anyone want to know what I think?

66
00:03:14,884 --> 00:03:17,429
Fine, I'll keep it to myself.

67
00:03:18,110 --> 00:03:19,187
I'm just saing...

68
00:03:19,188 --> 00:03:22,865
my entire workday is spent sorting
through my various clients' lies.

69
00:03:22,866 --> 00:03:24,331
This kid?

70
00:03:24,332 --> 00:03:25,791
I think he's on the up-and-up.

71
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,802
Okay.

72
00:03:32,186 --> 00:03:35,812
I've got an appointment with
Dean O'Dell's old assistant.

73
00:03:35,813 --> 00:03:37,965
I can't just put his murder case on hold.

74
00:03:40,519 --> 00:03:41,249
What?

75
00:03:41,634 --> 00:03:43,256
Just...

76
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:46,770
I thought this sight would be
more traumatic for me, but...

77
00:03:52,011 --> 00:03:52,832
Vincent!

78
00:03:56,136 --> 00:03:58,666
You bringing in a fugitive
or picking up your dad?

79
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:00,393
Old-timer, fraud warrant.

80
00:04:00,394 --> 00:04:03,877
Turns out, his uncle
isn't Nigerian royalty.

81
00:04:06,007 --> 00:04:07,561
Hey, uh, question.

82
00:04:08,715 --> 00:04:12,726
I saw what looked like an invoice from you
at the home of Coach Barry's widow.

83
00:04:12,727 --> 00:04:14,508
Any chance we're working the same case?

84
00:04:14,509 --> 00:04:15,551
Negatory.

85
00:04:15,552 --> 00:04:18,930
Mrs. Barry hired me about a month ago,
wanted to know if her husband was cheating.

86
00:04:18,931 --> 00:04:19,939
What'd you learn?

87
00:04:19,940 --> 00:04:24,530
Keith, I am bound by the exact
same ethical codes you are.

88
00:04:24,531 --> 00:04:26,182
Yeah, well-

89
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:29,488
I was pulling your leg. I had you, though.

90
00:04:29,489 --> 00:04:30,801
No. Never got a money shot,

91
00:04:30,802 --> 00:04:33,567
but I did catch him getting
friendly in a parking lot

92
00:04:33,568 --> 00:04:35,495
with a very attractive married lady.

93
00:04:35,684 --> 00:04:37,874
Any chance I could get
a copy of that picture?

94
00:04:37,875 --> 00:04:39,920
Yeah, what the hell? It'll be good
having you owe me one.

95
00:04:39,921 --> 00:04:41,526
I guess you're tracking that kid?

96
00:04:41,527 --> 00:04:43,143
I was thinking of diving into that.

97
00:04:43,144 --> 00:04:45,736
Well, I'm... looking for the coach's killer.

98
00:04:45,737 --> 00:04:46,942
Didn't you hear?

99
00:04:46,943 --> 00:04:48,164
It's the kid.

100
00:04:49,716 --> 00:04:52,366
I spoke to the Sheriff two
month ago, is there anything...

101
00:04:52,601 --> 00:04:55,142
Just routine follow-up on
some insurance matters.

102
00:04:55,143 --> 00:04:59,271
If you could just tell me anything you
can recall about the day the dean died.

103
00:04:59,272 --> 00:05:02,104
Just the usual stuff, meetings.

104
00:05:02,105 --> 00:05:04,406
There was one strange thing.

105
00:05:04,407 --> 00:05:08,368
Mel Stoltz showed up, no appointment.
I didn't know who he was until he left.

106
00:05:08,369 --> 00:05:09,962
He seemed to agitate Cyrus.

107
00:05:09,963 --> 00:05:11,828
Really? Mel Stoltz?

108
00:05:11,829 --> 00:05:12,786
Oh...

109
00:05:12,787 --> 00:05:17,147
and, um, he was out of Xanax.
I had to call in the prescription.

110
00:05:17,148 --> 00:05:18,798
Did he pick it up, do you know?

111
00:05:18,799 --> 00:05:22,621
Mmm, he was stuck here all day,
and the pharmacy closes at 7:00, so...

112
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:27,245
A prescription refill called
in on December 10th.

113
00:05:27,714 --> 00:05:29,823
Do you have a record of who picked it up?

114
00:05:30,796 --> 00:05:32,021
Bye.

115
00:05:34,453 --> 00:05:37,572
- Dr. Landry, what brings you-
- Question, Keith.

116
00:05:37,573 --> 00:05:39,389
I found this bug in my cell phone.

117
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:40,538
Did you put it here?

118
00:05:43,631 --> 00:05:46,163
- No, Hank.
- Did Veronica do it?

119
00:05:46,164 --> 00:05:48,041
I'm sure she had nothing to do with it.

120
00:05:48,042 --> 00:05:49,877
You're sure, sure?

121
00:05:49,878 --> 00:05:51,368
She's got a lot of initiative.

122
00:05:51,936 --> 00:05:53,278
You know, the other day,

123
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:56,624
she asked me something about the movie
that I watched in the hotel that night,

124
00:05:56,659 --> 00:05:59,679
and then I realised
she was probing my alibi.

125
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,452
She does have a lot of initiative.

126
00:06:01,453 --> 00:06:03,780
She also has got a lot of promise,

127
00:06:03,781 --> 00:06:05,755
and she doesn't need to be slumming it

128
00:06:05,756 --> 00:06:07,885
in a P.I. office the rest of her life.

129
00:06:07,886 --> 00:06:09,907
And, uh, just for the record,

130
00:06:09,908 --> 00:06:12,593
that night I checked into the Grand at 7:30.

131
00:06:12,594 --> 00:06:14,504
I watched the Clipper game in my room

132
00:06:14,505 --> 00:06:16,828
until Mindy showed up, about 8:15.

133
00:06:16,829 --> 00:06:20,404
The rest of the evening was occupied
by the usual business of an affair,

134
00:06:20,405 --> 00:06:22,931
followed by a pay-per-view
movie, then sleep.

135
00:06:22,932 --> 00:06:25,193
There's no more to say.

136
00:06:25,194 --> 00:06:27,509
And there's no more for you
or your daughter to find.

137
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:30,615
So please stop trying.
It's starting to piss me off.

138
00:06:33,974 --> 00:06:35,892
I need to see the Sheriff.

139
00:06:37,209 --> 00:06:39,519
I don't know, Keith. He looks kind of busy.

140
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:41,912
Well, that's something I got to see.

141
00:06:44,376 --> 00:06:46,426
So, if I'm hearing you right,
you're calling me a dumbass.

142
00:06:46,427 --> 00:06:50,303
All I said was the dean's death
was a murder, not a suicide.

143
00:06:50,304 --> 00:06:53,053
I wanted to bring you what
I had as a concerned citizen.

144
00:06:53,054 --> 00:06:54,325
You remember from the toxicology report

145
00:06:54,326 --> 00:06:56,664
he had traces of Xanax
in there with the booze.

146
00:06:56,676 --> 00:06:59,174
And he had a prescription for
the stuff which proves zilch.

147
00:06:59,175 --> 00:07:01,108
But according to his secretary,
he had run out.

148
00:07:01,109 --> 00:07:02,957
She'd just called in a new prescription,

149
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:06,265
which was picked up that night,
I learned, by Mindy O'Dell.

150
00:07:09,338 --> 00:07:10,757
Sacks.

151
00:07:12,085 --> 00:07:13,302
Call over to Hearst.

152
00:07:13,303 --> 00:07:14,858
See if they stored any of the dean's stuff.

153
00:07:14,859 --> 00:07:16,959
Computer, phone or whatever.
We can dust for prints.

154
00:07:16,994 --> 00:07:17,618
Sure Sheriff.

155
00:07:17,619 --> 00:07:20,464
And bring Mindy O'Dell in.
I'd like to ask her a few questions.

156
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,700
Veronica Mars

157
00:07:28,735 --> 00:07:31,735
3×14 "Mars Bars"

158
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:35,800
Transcript: Inigo [vmtranscripts.com]
Synchro: Camilla [veronicamars.it]

159
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,700
Vieni a trovarci!

160
00:07:49,701 --> 00:07:53,701
veronicamars.it

161
00:07:59,394 --> 00:08:00,914
You bring my harmonica?

162
00:08:00,915 --> 00:08:02,839
I've got the blues, pa,

163
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:06,417
the sittin'-in-my-jail-cell blues.

164
00:08:06,418 --> 00:08:08,139
Did you bug Hank Landry's phone?

165
00:08:08,140 --> 00:08:09,199
Wait, what?

166
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,469
He just came storming into the office,

167
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:13,168
saying he found a bug in his cell phone,

168
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:15,674
asking me if I planted it.
I didn't. Did you?

169
00:08:15,675 --> 00:08:16,755
No.

170
00:08:17,212 --> 00:08:18,709
Really.

171
00:08:19,035 --> 00:08:21,700
Come on dad, this is the face of truth.

172
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:23,876
Yeah, that played better
in a different context.

173
00:08:23,877 --> 00:08:25,909
But, okay, I'm a sucker. I believe you.

174
00:08:25,951 --> 00:08:29,630
Word of advice: you might want
to start looking for a new mentor.

175
00:08:29,631 --> 00:08:31,047
Wait. He suspected me?

176
00:08:31,048 --> 00:08:32,069
Vigorously.

177
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:34,528
Though he emphasised that
it was my bad influence.

178
00:08:34,529 --> 00:08:37,528
that you're a sharp kid,
just a bit misguided.

179
00:08:37,529 --> 00:08:38,995
The movie.

180
00:08:39,704 --> 00:08:42,722
He knew why I asked
about Kiss Kiss Bang Bang.

181
00:08:42,723 --> 00:08:44,008
You want to pick at his alibi,

182
00:08:44,009 --> 00:08:46,119
you should have asked him about
the Clippers game that night.

183
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:49,797
Men routinely accept the idea
that women don't know sports.

184
00:08:49,798 --> 00:08:50,990
That's just a...

185
00:08:50,991 --> 00:08:53,862
That's just a... mentoring sample,
for if you're interested.

186
00:08:53,863 --> 00:08:56,573
- You didn't bug him?
- No.

187
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,613
- Mr. Mars.
- Logan.

188
00:09:06,364 --> 00:09:08,579
Down the hall, on the right.

189
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,242
Logan?

190
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:18,347
No holiday decorations, huh?

191
00:09:19,126 --> 00:09:21,558
Actually, that's just why I'm in jail,

192
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:24,378
to avoid Valentine's day.

193
00:09:27,283 --> 00:09:28,625
Glad to see you.

194
00:09:28,626 --> 00:09:30,728
We're both adults now, right?

195
00:09:30,729 --> 00:09:32,495
We can be civil.

196
00:09:33,454 --> 00:09:34,824
Do you need anything?

197
00:09:34,825 --> 00:09:38,755
There is one thing you could do for me,
if you're heading back to campus.

198
00:09:39,403 --> 00:09:42,139
Get my wireless card back from the deputy.

199
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:44,735
I was taking it to Mac when I got arrested.

200
00:09:44,736 --> 00:09:47,950
She said she needed it for a thing tonight.

201
00:09:47,951 --> 00:09:49,007
Sure.

202
00:09:50,086 --> 00:09:51,497
Thanks.

203
00:09:51,498 --> 00:09:54,671
You've nearly warmed this
cold, cold heart of mine.

204
00:09:59,732 --> 00:10:01,637
Well, this definitely warms mine.

205
00:10:01,638 --> 00:10:03,311
You don't remember the movie?

206
00:10:03,312 --> 00:10:05,694
Hank must have ordered it
after I fell asleep.

207
00:10:05,695 --> 00:10:07,083
That's pretty late for a movie.

208
00:10:07,084 --> 00:10:11,204
Don't you think he'd have been pretty
tired after all your... activities?

209
00:10:11,205 --> 00:10:13,829
I guess that some people have stamina.

210
00:10:15,325 --> 00:10:17,690
- You didn't leave the room?
- No.

211
00:10:17,691 --> 00:10:20,029
Lying to me is a crime, you know.

212
00:10:21,088 --> 00:10:22,709
You might be thinking of perjury.

213
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:23,961
I am thinking of perjury.

214
00:10:23,962 --> 00:10:26,541
Well, then you might be
confused about what perjury is.

215
00:10:26,542 --> 00:10:29,215
Me lying to you here is not perjury.

216
00:10:29,216 --> 00:10:30,835
But I am not lying

217
00:10:30,836 --> 00:10:33,558
You're aware the dean had traces
of Xanax in his system?

218
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,987
Yes, and alcohol. They told me.

219
00:10:35,988 --> 00:10:37,890
Any idea where he got those pills?

220
00:10:37,891 --> 00:10:39,158
He had a prescription.

221
00:10:39,159 --> 00:10:40,094
Which had run out.

222
00:10:40,095 --> 00:10:41,972
Well, he must have had some left.

223
00:10:41,973 --> 00:10:45,601
Mrs. O'Dell, did you sign for a prescription
for Cyrus the night he was killed?

224
00:10:45,602 --> 00:10:46,439
Yes.

225
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,477
But you didn't see him after that.

226
00:10:48,478 --> 00:10:49,650
That's right.

227
00:10:49,651 --> 00:10:52,849
So if I found that bottle,
there wouldn't be any missing pills?

228
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:55,155
There are several missing.

229
00:10:55,156 --> 00:10:56,207
Where did they go?

230
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:57,507
I took them.

231
00:10:57,777 --> 00:11:01,549
My husband's suicide left me with
a certain amount of anxiety.

232
00:11:12,529 --> 00:11:15,017
One-three-zero-zero-four-seven-nine.
The former computer of Cyrus O'Dell.

233
00:11:15,346 --> 00:11:18,539
She's all yours.
Knock yourself out, Magnum.

234
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:23,693
- Logan!
- Hey.

235
00:11:23,694 --> 00:11:26,469
- Is Mac around?
- Yeah, come in.

236
00:11:27,614 --> 00:11:28,541
- Hey.
- Hi.

237
00:11:29,337 --> 00:11:31,693
Veronica ask me to bring you this.

238
00:11:32,473 --> 00:11:34,626
Performing a favor from a jail cell?

239
00:11:34,627 --> 00:11:36,448
The girl has serious friendship skills.

240
00:11:37,763 --> 00:11:40,183
Jason can't do it, either.
He's out of town.

241
00:11:40,184 --> 00:11:41,777
Oh..

242
00:11:42,607 --> 00:11:44,906
Logan, can we,

243
00:11:44,941 --> 00:11:46,764
like, borrow you?

244
00:11:47,317 --> 00:11:50,441
Will I be returned in my
current pristine condition?

245
00:11:50,442 --> 00:11:51,198
Yes.

246
00:11:51,399 --> 00:11:52,724
Go on.

247
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,326
So, big news today.

248
00:11:55,327 --> 00:11:57,732
Mason didn't show at practice and
no one's seen or heard from him.

249
00:11:57,733 --> 00:12:01,221
Any chance Mason is lying about
seeing Josh with his dad?

250
00:12:01,222 --> 00:12:02,404
