doing on his computer keyboard?

507
00:26:00,861 --> 00:26:02,705
You got to be...

508
00:26:02,706 --> 00:26:04,859
you think I killed that old bastard?

509
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:08,440
The last thing typed on his
keyboard was a suicide note,

510
00:26:08,441 --> 00:26:11,723
and whoever wrote it also put
a bullet in the dean's head.

511
00:26:13,988 --> 00:26:15,402
That bitch is setting me up.

512
00:26:15,403 --> 00:26:17,557
"That bitch" being your ex-wife?

513
00:26:19,148 --> 00:26:21,814
I'm done talking. I want a lawyer.

514
00:26:23,917 --> 00:26:25,387
You got it, Stevie.

515
00:26:26,961 --> 00:26:28,168
Mr. Batando?

516
00:26:31,534 --> 00:26:36,012
Brace yourself for the best free legal
representation in Neptune county.

517
00:26:37,178 --> 00:26:38,438
Do I know you?

518
00:26:38,887 --> 00:26:40,769
I've got one of those faces.

519
00:26:40,770 --> 00:26:42,602
I'd like to remind my client that

520
00:26:42,603 --> 00:26:46,278
he is answering these questions
only as a courtesy to the sheriff.

521
00:26:46,416 --> 00:26:47,658
Is that it?

522
00:26:47,659 --> 00:26:49,298
That's it for now.

523
00:26:50,214 --> 00:26:52,875
Mr. Batando, where were you
on the night of December 10th,

524
00:26:52,876 --> 00:26:54,404
- approximately-
- Hold on.

525
00:26:54,443 --> 00:26:58,328
It says here Mr. Batando was picked up
at the laundromat on El Camino.

526
00:26:58,329 --> 00:26:59,392
So?

527
00:26:59,393 --> 00:27:00,726
Just pointing out that

528
00:27:00,727 --> 00:27:05,688
my client was taken into custody a hundred
yards inside Santa Rita County.

529
00:27:05,689 --> 00:27:08,002
You don't have jurisdiction there.

530
00:27:08,203 --> 00:27:12,037
Any information you gather
today will be inadmissible.

531
00:27:12,038 --> 00:27:13,649
I'm sure you know that.

532
00:27:13,650 --> 00:27:15,096
Do go on.

533
00:27:30,709 --> 00:27:31,833
Mrs. Andriotti!

534
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:36,902
Keith Mars.

535
00:27:37,372 --> 00:27:38,576
Sorry to bother you.

536
00:27:38,577 --> 00:27:41,570
I'm a private investigator looking
into the death of Tom Barry.

537
00:27:42,417 --> 00:27:46,651
A few weeks before his death,
his wife hired another P.I. to follow him.

538
00:27:47,711 --> 00:27:49,862
She suspected he was having an affair.

539
00:27:51,455 --> 00:27:53,386
Mrs. Andriotti, if you know something...

540
00:27:54,677 --> 00:27:57,409
It's Dr. Andriotti. I'm a neurologist.

541
00:27:57,941 --> 00:27:59,568
Mr. Barry was a patient.

542
00:28:00,059 --> 00:28:01,099
He was sick?

543
00:28:01,100 --> 00:28:03,283
Have you heard of
Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease?

544
00:28:04,154 --> 00:28:05,443
He was terminal.

545
00:28:06,182 --> 00:28:08,291
And what he was about to go through...

546
00:28:08,714 --> 00:28:10,191
All I konw is...

547
00:28:10,192 --> 00:28:11,271
is whoever killed him

548
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:13,899
probably spared that
poor man a lot of suffering.

549
00:28:18,380 --> 00:28:19,931
You're alive.

550
00:28:19,932 --> 00:28:22,035
I'm always happy to come home and find

551
00:28:22,036 --> 00:28:24,872
my dad hasn't been shot by a naval officer.

552
00:28:24,873 --> 00:28:28,075
Some interesting twists
in the Coach Barry case.

553
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:33,222
It turns out the coach's wife took out an
additional life-insurance policy on her husband

554
00:28:33,223 --> 00:28:37,105
a couple of days after Vinnie showed her the
pictures of her husband with another woman.

555
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,055
Oh, my.

556
00:28:39,056 --> 00:28:40,380
And that's not all.

557
00:28:40,381 --> 00:28:43,422
The new policy had a
double-indemnity clause.

558
00:28:43,457 --> 00:28:46,210
If his death is ruled an accident-

559
00:28:46,211 --> 00:28:49,768
say, a carjacking/murder, for instance -

560
00:28:49,769 --> 00:28:51,451
it paid out double.

561
00:28:51,452 --> 00:28:55,464
As it stands, the family will be sitting
pretty with a five million dollar payout.

562
00:28:56,472 --> 00:29:00,661
Mrs. Barry was at home with the younger son
and the babysitter at the time of the murder.

563
00:29:00,662 --> 00:29:02,188
You think she hired somebody?

564
00:29:02,189 --> 00:29:04,378
That was my first thought, but with what?

565
00:29:04,379 --> 00:29:08,116
They took out a second mortgage to pay
for their younger son's medical expenses.

566
00:29:08,117 --> 00:29:10,875
It's not like they'd find ten
grand in the couch cushions.

567
00:29:11,206 --> 00:29:13,684
And it's not like hit men work on spec.

568
00:29:15,315 --> 00:29:16,418
Veronica?

569
00:29:16,419 --> 00:29:18,109
Nothing.

570
00:29:18,110 --> 00:29:19,535
Wait till you hear the kicker.

571
00:29:19,536 --> 00:29:21,103
The coach wasn't having an affair.

572
00:29:21,104 --> 00:29:23,431
The woman he was seeing is a neurologist.

573
00:29:23,432 --> 00:29:27,331
The coach was dying of
Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.

574
00:29:27,332 --> 00:29:30,943
It promised a grim, prolonged,
and expensive death.

575
00:29:31,351 --> 00:29:33,956
She may have actually done him a favour.

576
00:29:45,742 --> 00:29:47,346
Keith.

577
00:29:52,462 --> 00:29:54,281
Number Unavailable - Unknown.

578
00:29:55,327 --> 00:29:56,648
Josh?

579
00:30:02,140 --> 00:30:02,887
Here.

580
00:30:03,810 --> 00:30:05,274
Your new ID.

581
00:30:05,773 --> 00:30:07,064
Thanks, Veronica.

582
00:30:07,065 --> 00:30:08,149
Good luck.

583
00:30:12,761 --> 00:30:14,429
You think you're nervous now?

584
00:30:14,430 --> 00:30:17,663
What if you knew that there's a
chance those coins will be gone,

585
00:30:17,664 --> 00:30:21,555
and if they're gone, it means your
mother had your father killed?

586
00:30:22,641 --> 00:30:25,140
Mr. Mars, it sounds to me like you're asking

587
00:30:25,141 --> 00:30:28,836
if I had my son kill my husband
for insurance money.

588
00:30:28,837 --> 00:30:30,170
Not exactly.

589
00:30:31,184 --> 00:30:34,077
Wait here. I want to show you something.

590
00:30:40,195 --> 00:30:43,041
I need to get into my
safe deposit box, please.

591
00:30:43,042 --> 00:30:44,441
Can I see some ID?

592
00:31:01,890 --> 00:31:04,342
Here you go, Mr. Barry.
I'll give you your privacy.

593
00:31:23,624 --> 00:31:25,273
Mr. Mars?

594
00:31:38,127 --> 00:31:40,073
That's a colt .45.

595
00:31:40,943 --> 00:31:43,351
Something you want to tell me, Mrs. Barry?

596
00:32:02,426 --> 00:32:05,818
Mr. Mars, I was not planning to shoot you.

597
00:32:06,611 --> 00:32:09,467
That is so ridiculous.
I don't even know how to use a gun.

598
00:32:09,468 --> 00:32:10,736
You pull the trigger.

599
00:32:10,737 --> 00:32:13,795
Listen to me. I got the
gun to show it to you.

600
00:32:15,152 --> 00:32:19,123
When Josh told me that my husband was
killed and the police showed up,

601
00:32:19,124 --> 00:32:20,546
I hid it.

602
00:32:20,547 --> 00:32:21,797
Because he did it?

603
00:32:21,798 --> 00:32:24,260
Because I thought it would
make him look guilty.

604
00:32:25,465 --> 00:32:28,950
But then I read on the internet that
they can test them, can't they?

605
00:32:28,951 --> 00:32:31,099
That's why I wanted you to have it,

606
00:32:31,756 --> 00:32:34,010
to prove that my son is innocent.

607
00:32:37,965 --> 00:32:40,928
It was Tom's old gun from his army days.

608
00:32:43,961 --> 00:32:45,634
He coached there, you know.

609
00:32:54,241 --> 00:32:55,164
So?

610
00:32:58,180 --> 00:32:59,958
Relieved?

611
00:33:01,861 --> 00:33:03,501
This was in there, too.

612
00:33:03,502 --> 00:33:05,181
It's my dad's handwriting.

613
00:33:05,587 --> 00:33:07,265
Do you have any idea what it is?

614
00:33:07,266 --> 00:33:08,954
None.

615
00:33:12,898 --> 00:33:14,104
Hey, Keith.

616
00:33:14,105 --> 00:33:15,055
What's that?

617
00:33:15,056 --> 00:33:17,692
Something Mrs. Barry neglected to turn over.

618
00:33:17,693 --> 00:33:19,857
She wants it tested for powder residue.

619
00:33:19,858 --> 00:33:21,963
She thinks it'll help prove
her son didn't do it.

620
00:33:23,833 --> 00:33:25,041
Let's move, Sacks.

621
00:33:25,042 --> 00:33:26,094
Give me that address again.

622
00:33:26,095 --> 00:33:27,924
112 Delmar Circle.

623
00:33:27,925 --> 00:33:29,529
Something happen at the O'Dell's'?

624
00:33:29,530 --> 00:33:31,388
Yeah, another breaking-and-entering call.

625
00:33:31,389 --> 00:33:32,582
It's Batando.

626
00:33:32,583 --> 00:33:33,801
That's what I'm hoping.

627
00:33:33,802 --> 00:33:35,405
You want me to come along?

628
00:33:35,406 --> 00:33:39,745
It's just I've dealt with him before.
The guy's a little unhinged.

629
00:33:39,746 --> 00:33:41,004
I think I can handle it, Keith,

630
00:33:41,005 --> 00:33:43,919
but I'll tell you what.
I'll give you a call if I need any backup.

631
00:33:57,409 --> 00:33:59,128
Make sure he doesn't slip out.

632
00:34:12,287 --> 00:34:14,424
You better hide, you crazy bitch!

633
00:34:55,377 --> 00:34:57,402
You like that?! Huh?!

634
00:35:06,407 --> 00:35:07,606
Sheriff?

635
00:35:09,209 --> 00:35:10,151
I...

636
00:35:10,152 --> 00:35:13,050
I s-smell bread.

637
00:35:16,500 --> 00:35:17,298
Sacks!

638
00:35:21,376 --> 00:35:22,412
Sacks.

639
00:35:23,673 --> 00:35:27,232
I need for you to go call
for an ambulance now.

640
00:35:46,789 --> 00:35:48,491
Son, if you're watching this,

641
00:35:48,492 --> 00:35:50,192
you're twenty-one years old,

642
00:35:50,193 --> 00:35:51,890
I'm long gone,

643
00:35:51,891 --> 00:35:55,835
and the statute of limitations has
run out on our insurance claim.

644
00:35:55,836 --> 00:35:57,522
It's time you know.

645
00:35:57,891 --> 00:36:00,591
I was responsible for my own death.

646
00:36:02,242 --> 00:36:04,376
Joshua, as I make this tape,

647
00:36:04,377 --> 00:36:06,884
I'm dying of a disease

648
00:36:06,885 --> 00:36:09,855
that will sap me of my mind and

649
00:36:09,905 --> 00:36:11,905
our financial resources.

650
00:36:13,109 --> 00:36:15,137
I had my first attack today.

651
00:36:16,205 --> 00:36:19,211
And I won't allow myself to have another.

652
00:36:19,212 --> 00:36:21,587
I didn't want to go out like that,

653
00:36:21,871 --> 00:36:24,949
but I won't leave our
family destitute, either.

654
00:36:26,350 --> 00:36:29,181
The person I asked to
help me wasn't a killer.

655
00:36:29,182 --> 00:36:33,427
He was a dear friend who knew everything.

656
00:36:33,428 --> 00:36:35,923
Son, please know that I am proud of you.

657
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:38,580
I know I was tough on you,

658
00:36:38,581 --> 00:36:41,603
but I was preparing you
to be man of the house.

659
00:36:43,148 --> 00:36:45,543
I leave this earth with no doubt

660
00:36:45,578 --> 00:36:49,548
you've taken good care of your mother
and brother the past couple of years.

661
00:36:49,776 --> 00:36:52,139
That's simply the kind of man you are.

662
00:37:06,618 --> 00:37:07,775
Josh,

663
00:37:08,339 --> 00:37:10,215
there's someone else in the room.

664
00:37:13,341 --> 00:37:14,773
It looks like you.

665
00:37:16,478 --> 00:37:17,978
That's,

666
00:37:17,979 --> 00:37:19,526
uh, that's Coach Yeager.

667
00:37:20,046 --> 00:37:22,704
He was my dad's assistant coach.
He played for him at army.

668
00:37:22,705 --> 00:37:24,421
That's who Mason saw.

669
00:37:36,126 --> 00:37:39,480
They said on the radio that Sheriff
Lamb is still in intensive care.

670
00:37:41,372 --> 00:37:42,550
My buddy in customs found

671
00:37:42,551 --> 00:37:45,139
footage of Josh crossing
the border on a fake ID.

672
00:37:45,174 --> 00:37:46,789
Please tell me it's just a coincidence.

673
00:37:46,790 --> 00:37:49,125
- Dad-
- You want to give me plausible deniability?

674
00:37:49,126 --> 00:37:53,536
I suggest you remember to unplug
the laminator next time.

675
00:37:55,426 --> 00:37:56,734
Why, Veronica?

676
00:37:56,735 --> 00:37:58,468
You know Josh didn't do it.

677
00:37:58,469 --> 00:38:00,971
Only guilty people flee the country, honey.

678
00:38:00,972 --> 00:38:02,815
Here's something you need to see.

679
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:12,464
Mars Investigations.

680
00:38:13,970 --> 00:38:16,108
The same thing happens every year.

681
00:38:16,983 --> 00:38:18,874
"Heat's not working."

682
00:38:18,875 --> 00:38:21,152
"The furnace smells bad."

683
00:38:21,153 --> 00:38:23,390
Wah, wah, wah.

684
00:38:24,555 --> 00:38:27,394
Hell, the thing's as old as
the damn university.

685
00:38:29,945 --> 00:38:33,313
Trustees might as well put it
on the historical registry.

686
00:38:34,474 --> 00:38:37,271
Look at that. Rusted clear through.

687
00:38:37,867 --> 00:38:39,316
Hey, Weevil,

688
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:41,865
why don't you clean the flue,
long as we're down here, huh?

689
00:38:42,657 --> 00:38:43,741
Sure.

690
00:39:08,424 --> 00:39:09,632
Whoa.

691
00:39:09,633 --> 00:39:10,772
Boss,

692
00:39:11,753 --> 00:39:13,076
I think you should see this.

693
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,684
That's simply the kind of man you are.

694
00:39:25,590 --> 00:39:27,706
It's the County Commissioner's office.

695
00:39:28,709 --> 00:39:30,434
So, Josh is planning to stay gone

696
00:39:30,435 --> 00:39:32,677
until his family's insurance money is safe?

697
00:39:32,712 --> 00:39:33,745
That's his plan.

698
00:39:34,630 --> 00:39:36,780
He said he'd try to get
in touch with his mom,

699
00:39:37,251 --> 00:39:38,485
tell her what really happened,

700
00:39:38,486 --> 00:39:43,862
but that it was more important for her and
his little brother to be taken care of.

701
00:39:43,863 --> 00:39:45,991
He said it was...

702
00:39:45,992 --> 00:39:48,626
time for him to be a man.

703
00:39:50,326 --> 00:39:51,239
Dad,

704
00:39:51,582 --> 00:39:53,064
the County Commissioner.

705
00:39:55,713 --> 00:39:57,236
This is Keith Mars.

706
00:39:58,433 --> 00:40:00,122
Sure, Commissioner.

707
00:40:00,946 --> 00:40:02,198
No.

708
00:40:03,703 --> 00:40:04,909
What?

709
00:40:07,291 --> 00:40:09,058
I'm very sorry to hear that.

710
00:40:12,963 --> 00:40:13,759
Of course.

711
00:40:15,373 --> 00:40:17,195
First thing in the morning, fine.

712
00:40:18,816 --> 00:40:20,141
Okay. Goodbye.

713
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:29,764
He, uh...

714
00:40:32,682 --> 00:40:35,056
He says Sheriff Lamb's dead.

715
00:40:42,997 --> 00:40:44,787
I can't believe Josh did it and

716
00:40:44,788 --> 00:40:45,875
just disappeared.

717
00:40:47,227 --> 00:40:49,306
How awful for that guy's family.

718
00:41:09,138 --> 00:41:11,992
I really don't understand why
you had to drag me down here-

719
00:41:14,074 --> 00:41:16,569
I know. I'm a tough man
to shake, Mrs. O'Dell.

720
00:41:18,707 --> 00:41:20,227
What do you want, Keith?

721
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:21,944
Sheriff Mars.

722
00:41:24,062 --> 00:41:27,254
Two maintenance workers found a
bag of bloody clothes on campus.

723
00:41:34,372 --> 00:41:36,866
The shirt belongs to your
boyfriend, Hank Landry.

724
00:41:37,500 --> 00:41:38,719
So, here's the deal.

725
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:41,772
Either you're covering for him,
or he's covering for you,

726
00:41:41,773 --> 00:41:44,076
and you're gonna
tell me which it is right now.

